<li>Sir Matthew Digby Wyatt, 1820–1877. <em>Metal-work and its Artistic Design</em>. London: Day and Son, 1852. <em>The Frontispiece: being a Design for a precious Book-cover, introducing many of the most elaborate processes of Metal Working</em>. Plate.</li>
<li>British Museum Department of Manuscripts. <em>Illuminated Manuscripts in the British Museum: miniatures, borders, and initials, reproduced in gold and colours / with descriptive text by George F. Warner ... Series I-IV</em>. London: Printed by order of the Trustees [by W. Griggs], 1899–1901. <em>Arundel Ms. 83</em> (Psalter, early xiv. century, English).</li></ol>
